<subSubSection id="C374657AC311FF98FF419AAE5D9043FD" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BD136F1C311FF98FF419AAE5B6740DD" blockId="10.[151,1436,402,789]" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">
<emphasis id="B91AEAE3C311FF98FF419AAE5F2040A0" bold="true" box="[151,307,402,428]" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">Distribution:</emphasis>
Western Amazonia in 
<collectingCountry id="F3797661C311FF98FDE59AAF5C6940A1" box="[563,634,403,429]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3797661C311FF98FD509AAF5CAF40A1" box="[646,700,403,429]" name="Peru" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">Peru</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3797661C311FF98FD119AAF5D3540A1" box="[711,806,403,429]" name="Ecuador" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F3797661C311FF98FCB49AAF5DC340A1" box="[866,976,403,429]" name="Colombia" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B00C311FF98FC099AAF5B5340A1" author="Ribeiro-Junior, M. A. &amp; Amaral, S." box="[991,1344,403,429]" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" pagination="151 - 196" refId="ref18425" refString="Ribeiro-Junior, M. A. &amp; Amaral, S. (2017) Catalogue of distribution of lizards (Reptilia: Squamata) from the Brazilian Amazonia. IV. Alopoglossidae, Gymnophthalmidae. Zootaxa, 4269 (2), 151 - 196. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4269.2.1" type="journal article" year="2017">Ribeiro-Júnior &amp; Amaral 2017</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry id="F3797661C311FF98FAA49AAF5EF640DD" name="Colombia" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">Colombia</collectingCountry>
it is mainly distributed within the Amazonia region, with some records in southern Orinoquia (
<figureCitation id="13552A74C311FF98FAD99A8B5B7B40DD" box="[1295,1384,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1888,1912]" captionTargetBox="[217,1370,181,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-22@4.[217,1370,181,1864]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Distribution maps for the cis-Andean microteiid lizards in Colombia (Alopoglossidae + Gymnophthalmidae). Circles are examined specimens, while squares are records from literature (see Supplementary Files for specific references). Red arrows indicate new records for Colombia. Black arrows show a zoom in to regions where several records overlap. The light green shadow indicates the Orinoco River basin, and the dark green the Amazon River basin." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5681929" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5681929/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD136F1C311FF98FF119AE65D9043FD" blockId="10.[151,1436,402,789]" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">
<emphasis id="B91AEAE3C311FF98FF119AE65F9040F8" bold="true" box="[199,387,474,500]" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">Similar species:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D72C311FF98FE5D9AE75CA940F9" baseAuthorityName="Boulenger" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[395,698,475,501]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Cercosaura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oshaughnessyi">
<emphasis id="B91AEAE3C311FF98FE5D9AE75CA940F9" box="[395,698,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">Cercosaura oshaughnessyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from its congeners in having 11–17 longitudinal rows of enlarged hexagonal dorsal scales forming transversal lines, and a divided frontonasal (dorsal hexagonal scales arranged in transverse and oblique series in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D72C311FF98FD01991F5D794331" authorityName="Doan &amp; Lamar" authorityYear="2012" box="[727,874,547,573]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Cercosaura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hypnoides">
<emphasis id="B91AEAE3C311FF98FD01991F5D794331" box="[727,874,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">C. hypnoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, eight longitudinal rows in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D72C311FF98FB06991F5B5F4331" box="[1232,1356,547,573]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Cercosaura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ocellata">
<emphasis id="B91AEAE3C311FF98FB06991F5B5F4331" box="[1232,1356,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">C. ocellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, and a single frontonasal in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D72C311FF98FE2A997B5C6A436D" box="[508,633,583,609]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Cercosaura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ocellata">
<emphasis id="B91AEAE3C311FF98FE2A997B5C6A436D" box="[508,633,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">C. ocellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D72C311FF98FD29997B5D87436D" authorityName="Doan &amp; Lamar" authorityYear="2012" box="[767,916,583,609]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Cercosaura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hypnoides">
<emphasis id="B91AEAE3C311FF98FD29997B5D87436D" box="[767,916,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">C. hypnoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); and scales on flanks distinctly smaller than dorsals, 31–45 scales around midbody, presence of preanal pores, and two ventral scales separated by the femoral pores (scales on flanks moderately smaller than dorsals, 27–35 scales around midbody, absence of preanal pores, and four ventral scales separated by the femoral pores in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D72C311FF98FCE7998F5DBA43C1" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1862" box="[817,937,691,717]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Cercosaura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="argulus">
<emphasis id="B91AEAE3C311FF98FCE7998F5DBA43C1" box="[817,937,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">C. argulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). See 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B00C311FF98FC2399885AD843C1" author="Avila-Pires, T." box="[1013,1227,690,719]" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" pagination="1 - 706" refId="ref15408" refString="Avila-Pires, T. (1995) Lizards of Brazilian Amazonia (Reptilia: Squamata). Zoologische Verhandelingen, 299, 1 - 706." type="journal article" year="1995">Ávila-Pires (1995)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B00C311FF98FB0F998F5F2C43FD" author="Ribeiro-Junior, M. A. &amp; Amaral, S." pageId="10" pageNumber="387" pagination="151 - 196" refId="ref18425" refString="Ribeiro-Junior, M. A. &amp; Amaral, S. (2017) Catalogue of distribution of lizards (Reptilia: Squamata) from the Brazilian Amazonia. IV. Alopoglossidae, Gymnophthalmidae. Zootaxa, 4269 (2), 151 - 196. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4269.2.1" type="journal article" year="2017">Ribeiro-Júnior &amp; Amaral (2017)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFF4B00C311FF98FEAC99EB5C4E43FD" author="Sturaro, M. J. &amp; Rodrigues, M. T. &amp; Colli, G. R. &amp; Knowles, L. L. &amp; Avila-Pires, T. C." box="[378,605,727,753]" pageId="10" pageNumber="387" pagination="37 - 65" refId="ref19384" refString="Sturaro, M. J., Rodrigues, M. T., Colli, G. R., Knowles, L. L. &amp; Avila-Pires, T. C. (2018) Integrative taxonomy of the lizards Cercosaura ocellata species complex (Reptilia: Gymnophthalmidae). Zoologischer Anzeiger, 275, 37 - 65. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. jcz. 2018.04.004" type="journal article" year="2018">
Sturaro 
<emphasis id="B91AEAE3C311FF98FE0299EB5C1F43FD" box="[468,524,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="387">et al.</emphasis>
(2018)
</bibRefCitation>
for a detailed description.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
